.NET bindings for Hydna
=======================


Current version only supports Hydna Push.


Example
-------

Quick example how to send data to a specific channel using C#:

      using Hydna.Net;

      // Create a new HttpApiClient
      HttpApiClient client = HttpApiClient.create("public.hydna.net");

      // Send a "Hello world" message to the channel.
      client.Send("Hello world from C#");


Qucik exmaple how to send data a specific channel Async using C#:

      using Hydna.Net;

      // Create a new HttpApiClient
      HttpApiClient client = HttpApiClient.create("public.hydna.net");

      // Begin the send async operation channel.
      IAsyncResult result = client.BeginSend("Hello world from C#", null, null);

      // Wait for the response
      result.AsyncWaitHandle.WaitOne();

      // End the async operation.
      client.EndSend(result);



Future goals
------------

- Full support for bi-directional Hydna Channels
- Support for .NET 2 or higher, Silverlight, Windows Phone and Windows 8